    public class AttributeValidatorListener
extends AbstractListener
implements SourceEndExportNodeEventListener, TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener
    Listener which validates attributes on a node based on its regex value

      • setErrorLogMessage

        public void setErrorLogMessage(java.lang.String value)
        Injected, OPTIONAL. Message which will be included in the MigrationNode detailed log in case of error. Can include tokens that are resolved using properties on the node. If not set, "Validation failed for attribute " + injected attribute names will be used.

      • setFailIfNotFound

        public void setFailIfNotFound(boolean value)
        Injected, OPTIONAL. Boolean indicating whether or not validation should fail if the attribute is not found on the node. Defaults to true.

      • setValidationAttributeName

        public void setValidationAttributeName(java.lang.String value)
        Injected, OPTIONAL. Node attribute to set as true or false based on the validation outcome.

      • setAttributes

        public void setAttributes(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> attributes)
        Injected, REQUIRED. Map of attributes with their corresponding regex values

      • setFailNodeIfValidationFails

        public void setFailNodeIfValidationFails(boolean failNodeIfValidationFails)
        Injected, OPTIONAL. Whether or not to fail the node if the node fails validation. Defaults to true.

      • setInvertValidatorCriteria

        public void setInvertValidatorCriteria(boolean invertValidatorCriteria)
        Injected, OPTIONAL. Boolean indicating whether to invert the validation result. Defaults to false.

      • setValidateAssociations

        public void setValidateAssociations(boolean validateAssociations)
        Injected, OPTIONAL. Boolean indicating whether to run the associations through the validation as well. Defaults to true.
